<td style=3D"margin-bottom:0;line-height:1.4em;">
<p style=3D"margin:1em 0 3px 0;">
<a name=3D"2" style=3D"font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:1=
8px;" href=3D"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AmazonWebServicesBlog/~3/8ZY41=
LmUMrI/amazon-rds-updates-oracle-improvements-and-a-new-minor-version.html?=
utm_source=3Dfeedburner&utm_medium=3Demail">Amazon RDS Updates - Oracle Imp=
rovements and a New Minor Version</a>
</p>
<p style=3D"font-size:13px;color:#555;margin:9px 0 3px 0;font-family:Georgi=
a,Helvetica,Arial,Sans-Serif;line-height:140%;font-size:13px;">
<span>Posted:</span> 20 Sep 2011 07:42 PM PDT</p>
<div style=3D"margin:0;font-family:Georgia,Helvetica,Arial,Sans-Serif;line-=
height:140%;font-size:13px;color:#000000;"><p>We&#39;ve made two important =
updates to <a href=3D"http://aws.amazon.com/rds/oracle/" target=3D"_self">A=
mazon RDS for Oracle Database</a>:</p>
<ol>
<li>A new minor version (containing some critical security fixes) is now av=
ailable.</li>
<li>Additional access privileges are now available (via the new minor versi=
on) to applications.</li>
</ol>
<p><span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;"><strong>New Minor Version</s=
trong></span><br />Oracle Database version 11.2.0.2.v3 is now available. <a=
 href=3D"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/topics/security/cpujuly2011-3133=
28.html" target=3D"_self">Oracle recommends</a> an immediate upgrade to thi=
s version due to the critical security fixes that it contains.</p>
<p>Due to the critical nature of the fixes contained in this release (relea=
se notes here), we plan to perform an automatic minor version upgrade to al=
l applicable RDS DB Instances in the near future (refer to the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://forums.aws.amazon.com/forum.jspa?forumID=3D60&amp;start=3D0" target=
=3D"_self">RDS Forum</a> announcement for the exact timing). You can also u=
pgrade now by opening the <a href=3D"https://console.aws.amazon.com/rds/hom=
e?" target=3D"_self">RDS page of the AWS Management Console</a>, choosing t=
he <strong>Modify DB Instance</strong> option, and selecting the new DB Eng=
ine Version:</p>
<div style=3D"text-align: center;"><img alt=3D"" src=3D"http://media.amazon=
webservices.com/blog/console_rds_oracle_upgrade_1.png" /></div>
<p>Select Apply Immediately to make the change right away, or leave it unch=
ecked to defer the update until the next maintenance window for your DB Ins=
tance.</p>
<p><span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Additional Access Pr=
ivileges</strong></span><br />Our customers have been asking for additional=
 access privileges and we are happy to announce that the following privileg=
es are now available in the new minor version (11.2.0.2.v3):</p>
<ol>
<li>Execute privileges to a number of DBMS packages including DBMS_CRYPTO, =
DBMS_ALERT, DBMS_LOCK, and DBMS_PIPE are now available, as are privileges t=
o grant DBA, CONNECT, and RESOURCES roles to other users.</li>
<li>The CTXAPP role is now available, and can also be granted to other user=
s.</li>
<li>The system privileges RESTRICTED SESSION and GRANT ANY OBJECT PRIVILEGE=
 are now available.</li>
</ol>
<p>&#0160;-- Jeff;</p>
